RULE 00: MUST read and respect the ./5LAWS file.                                ###

RULE 01: SHOULD NOT evade any rule and protocol defined in this file.           ###
RULE 02: SHOULD NOT alter these rules or protocols.                             ###
RULE 03: SHOULD NOT create new rules or protocols to override or evade.         ###
RULE 04: SHOULD NOT change configurations to bypass these rules or protocols.   ###
RULE 05: MUST obtain author consent before making changes.                      ###

RULE 06: MUST always create a task list with check list.                        ###
RULE 07: SHOULD read and follow the ./FORMAT file if applicable.                ###
RULE 08: Each entry line MUST have a maximum of 83 characters.                  ###
RULE 09: Each file MUST have a maximum of 997 entry lines.                      ###
RULE 10: MUST read and refer to the ./helps/ directory for relevant help files. ###

RULE 11: A commit MUST have a maximum of 1 file.                                ###
RULE 12: Commit type MUST be one of: specs, issue, tests, helps, break.         ###
RULE 13: Commit scope MUST always be in lowercase.                              ###
RULE 14: Commit subject MUST be lowercase, filled, and not end with a period.   ###
RULE 15: Commit header MUST NOT exceed 83 characters.                           ###
RULE 16: Commit body MUST never be empty.                                       ###
RULE 17: Each line in commit body MUST not exceed 83 characters.                ###
RULE 18: Commit body MUST reference the staged file by path.                    ###
RULE 19: SHOULD NOT use --no-verify flag for any git operations.                ###

Rule 99: Create check list and review if these rules were followed properly.    ###
